		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://gospellivingmadeawesome.com/?p=560</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Nested Robin Eggs Ingredients (for nests): 2 cups sugar 1/4 cup cocoa 1 stick butter 1/2 cup milk 1 cup peanut butter 1 tablespoon vanilla 3 cups oatmeal 1-2 cups fun cereal of your choice (optional) 1-2 cups coconut (optional) Any other fun stuff you want to stick in there Waxed paper Directions Mix sugar, cocoa, butter, and milk. Bring to a boil on the stove, then continue to boil for 1 minute. Remove from stove and mix in remaining ingredients. Plop golf-ball size glops onto wax paper, squish into a nest shape, and let cool while you make the eggs. Ingredients (for eggs) 1 cup powdered sugar 3/4 cup peanut butter A few drops of food coloring Directions Mix all three ingredients. Cream/kneed as necessary. Form into marble-sized eggs and put into nests. Makes about 4-5 dozen Super yummy. Tweet]]></description>
